  "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. The line has the form <i>y</i> = <i>mx</i> + <i>b</i> with slope <i>m</i> = &frac17; and <i>y</i>-intercept (0, 12), so <i>b</i> = 12. Thus <i>y</i> = &frac17;<i>x</i> + 12.</p><p>Choices A, B, and D are incorrect: each uses the wrong sign for the slope or the wrong sign for the <i>y</i>-intercept.</p>",
